teething kittens my kitten who is weeks old bites me a lot i know he's playing and we've established play nips and real biting which he gets yelled at if he does but it got me thinking he's doing it more now as he's teething i never knew kittens did this until i read it can someone let me know exactly how long it takes kittens to teeth and where are the baby teeth likely to fall out when he's eating also he loves to sleep on my neck and follow me around will he be this cute always or grow out of it hiya jj iv fostered kittens for years for the rspca and until i read your question i never knew that kittens could have teething problems that just goes to show you learn something new everyday i have never found tiny teeth around the house so i guess they must fall out whilst their eating that's a guess remember iv always found that they stop chewing on you by about twelve weeks old don't know why but that's wot iv observed as for staying cute that's up to you most people get fed up of the cute stage and start pushing them away once they get bigger and don't look so cute any more iv always encouraged mine to stay loving and playful and its worked a treat if its in their nature and you actively encourage it they ll carry on enjoy your bundle of fluff x Garfield Kitten Dog training Tooth Guinea pig Dog Humphrey Bogart Cat Phoebe Buffay's songs Breastfeeding Non-Hodgkin's lymphoma Squirrel Cuteness Domestic rabbit Atomic Kitten Milton H. Erickson Little Britain Piccolo Junior Saga Kodocha Jon Secada Socialization Pet skunk The Lion, the Witch and the Wardrobe Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an Happy Tree Friends Stomach cancer Girly The Life and Times of Juniper Lee Episodes of Lost (Season 1) Avenue Q Physical attractiveness Friends The Fairly OddParents Ferret Pitaten Characters in the Smurfs Ed, Edd n Eddy Richard Rahl Shark Theory of conduct RuneScape quests Cats (musical) Pok__mon Live! The Amber Spyglass Rabbit Socrates EastEnders Eutheism, dystheism, and m